Usage: compare_release [-help] [-out_file <out_file>] {-base_version <version> | -base_file <in_file>} [-target_version <version> | -target_file <in_file>]

-help                         # Prints out the command usage
-base_file <in_file>          # Older base release .info file
                              # (string, optional)
-base_version <version>       # Older base release (e.g 16.10-p001_1) from
                              # <install>/share/innovus/version_info
                              # (string, optional)
-out_file <out_file>          # Output report file. Default is stdout
                              # (string, optional)
-target_file <in_file>        # Compare target release .info file to older base
                              # release .info file (string, optional)
-target_version <version>     # Default is current version. Compare this  (e.g
                              # 16.20-p002_1) to older base release. Looks in
                              # <install>/share/innovus/version_info for
                              # correct .info file (string, optional)